he development and survival of livestock gastrointestinal parasites on pastures, but that this can be overridden by the effect of high rainfall.$\backslash$n$\backslash$n$\backslash$n* Synthesis and applications. The work demonstrates that conservation of dung beetle populations in temperate climates is important in livestock management, not only for their essential role in dung degradation and nutrient cycling, but because their activity can also reduce the survival and availability of gastrointestinal parasites on pastures.$\backslash$n$\backslash$n},
